00:00:11.302 --> 00:00:13.763 position:50% align:center
[INOSE]
You guys, please wait!

00:00:13.847 --> 00:00:15.306 position:50% align:center
--Huh?
--Huh?

00:00:15.390 --> 00:00:18.476 position:50% align:center
Look, I understand how you feel,
but we're not allowed to use

00:00:18.560 --> 00:00:20.812 position:50% align:center
guerilla recruitment tactics!

00:00:20.895 --> 00:00:23.773 position:50% align:center
Huh? I didn't know that.

00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:25.025 position:50% align:center
We're sorry...

00:00:25.108 --> 00:00:27.736 position:50% align:center
Guess we got
a bit ahead of ourselves.

00:00:27.819 --> 00:00:29.696 position:50% align:center
For now, why don't we
all just take this conversation

00:00:29.779 --> 00:00:32.073 position:50% align:center
back to the classroom?

00:00:32.157 --> 00:00:34.826 position:50% align:center
I'll start by getting
permission from the school.

00:00:34.909 --> 00:00:36.327 position:50% align:center
Once we have that,
we can recruit members

00:00:36.411 --> 00:00:38.455 position:50% align:center
however we want, within reason.

00:00:38.538 --> 00:00:39.956 position:50% align:center
--[BOTH] Great!
--In the meantime,

00:00:40.040 --> 00:00:42.667 position:50% align:center
I've got work to do.
This sign needs one more dog!

00:00:42.751 --> 00:00:43.668 position:50% align:center
Does it?

00:00:43.752 --> 00:00:44.919 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Hey, hey!

00:00:45.003 --> 00:00:47.088 position:50% align:center
Huh? Hey, there, Suzu!

00:00:47.172 --> 00:00:48.256 position:50% align:center
Huh?!

00:00:48.798 --> 00:00:50.383 position:50% align:center
Making a spectacle
of yourselves this early

00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:52.177 position:50% align:center
in the school year, huh?

00:00:52.260 --> 00:00:54.304 position:50% align:center
Everyone in my class
was talking about it.

00:00:54.387 --> 00:00:56.097 position:50% align:center
I had to investigate.

00:00:56.181 --> 00:00:57.891 position:50% align:center
Whoa, Suzu. Your hair!

00:00:57.974 --> 00:00:59.225 position:50% align:center
What happened to it?

00:00:59.309 --> 00:01:01.978 position:50% align:center
Oh. Yeah, you haven't
seen me since I cut it,

00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:03.355 position:50% align:center
have you, Ino?

00:01:03.438 --> 00:01:05.482 position:50% align:center
Spring's the time
for rebirth, right?

00:01:05.565 --> 00:01:09.110 position:50% align:center
I'm Suzu Version Two,
nice to meet ya!

00:01:09.194 --> 00:01:10.820 position:50% align:center
It does look great on you.

00:01:10.904 --> 00:01:12.447 position:50% align:center
It's just such a big change!

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.032 position:50% align:center
Here's the real story.

00:01:14.115 --> 00:01:16.868 position:50% align:center
She had grown it out 'cause
she wanted to be like my sister.

00:01:16.951 --> 00:01:20.038 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
But... Misa and I had a talk.

00:01:20.121 --> 00:01:22.665 position:50% align:center
She said I should just be
myself instead of trying to

00:01:22.749 --> 00:01:24.959 position:50% align:center
be like her,
and I think she's right!

00:01:25.043 --> 00:01:26.044 position:50% align:center
Me, too!

00:01:26.127 --> 00:01:27.671 position:50% align:center
And it seems like
the public agrees,

00:01:27.754 --> 00:01:30.173 position:50% align:center
since business is
booming at the bakery!

00:01:30.256 --> 00:01:33.635 position:50% align:center
Jeez. How could I ever
repay Misa for all she's done?

00:01:33.718 --> 00:01:35.637 position:50% align:center
I gotta say no one knows
how to get attention

00:01:35.720 --> 00:01:37.305 position:50% align:center
like you, Suzu.

00:01:37.389 --> 00:01:40.183 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] So, what was up
with your parade earlier?

00:01:40.266 --> 00:01:42.769 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] There are only three of
us in the Earth Sciences Club.

00:01:42.852 --> 00:01:45.271 position:50% align:center
I want to ensure that
our club continues.

00:01:45.355 --> 00:01:48.191 position:50% align:center
So people can be in it,
even after we graduate!

00:01:48.274 --> 00:01:51.611 position:50% align:center
Hey, you're starting
to sound like a Vice President!

00:01:51.695 --> 00:01:54.823 position:50% align:center
Yeah, and, also, if we
can recruit more club members,

00:01:54.906 --> 00:01:56.533 position:50% align:center
we'll be able to
get more funding.

00:01:56.616 --> 00:01:57.992 position:50% align:center
Wow...

00:01:58.076 --> 00:01:59.703 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
No! Don't judge us!

00:01:59.786 --> 00:02:01.246 position:50% align:center
We don't want new
club members just so we can

00:02:01.329 --> 00:02:03.039 position:50% align:center
buy an equatorial mount!

00:02:03.123 --> 00:02:04.249 position:50% align:center
You sure?

00:02:04.332 --> 00:02:05.750 position:50% align:center
Waaah...!

00:02:05.834 --> 00:02:08.003 position:50% align:center
[INOSE]
Ahem. All right, friends.

00:02:08.086 --> 00:02:10.505 position:50% align:center
Let's work out a new
member recruitment plan!

00:02:10.588 --> 00:02:13.967 position:50% align:center
--Okay!
--Yeah, let's do our best!

00:02:14.050 --> 00:02:15.385 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Excuse me.

00:02:15.468 --> 00:02:17.846 position:50% align:center
Oh. Hi, come on in.

00:02:17.929 --> 00:02:20.306 position:50% align:center
I'd like to join
the Earth Sciences Club.

00:02:20.390 --> 00:02:22.267 position:50% align:center
Yes, me, too. What she said.

00:02:24.686 --> 00:02:26.146 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Huh?

00:03:57.946 --> 00:04:00.448 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] We haven't even
started recruiting yet

00:04:00.532 --> 00:04:02.325 position:50% align:center
and they wanna join up?

00:04:02.409 --> 00:04:04.911 position:50% align:center
[AO] Seems like our parade
this morning might have worked.

00:04:04.994 --> 00:04:07.122 position:50% align:center
I'm Yuu Nanami, a first-year.

00:04:07.205 --> 00:04:10.583 position:50% align:center
What she said,
except I'm Chikage Sakurai.

00:04:10.667 --> 00:04:11.584 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:04:11.668 --> 00:04:12.794 position:50% align:center
You're a Sakurai?

00:04:12.877 --> 00:04:16.131 position:50% align:center
Wait, are you
our Sakura's younger sister?

00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:17.674 position:50% align:center
Thank you all
for taking such good care

00:04:17.757 --> 00:04:19.968 position:50% align:center
of my big sister last year.

00:04:20.051 --> 00:04:22.721 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] I can totally
see the resemblance now!

00:04:22.804 --> 00:04:24.848 position:50% align:center
Nice to meet you, President Ino.

00:04:24.931 --> 00:04:26.182 position:50% align:center
Oh. Likewise!

00:04:26.266 --> 00:04:28.309 position:50% align:center
Hey, your sister told me
that you participated in

00:04:28.393 --> 00:04:32.897 position:50% align:center
the Earth Science Olympiad.
I participated last year, too.

00:04:32.981 --> 00:04:34.566 position:50% align:center
I remember, you were loud.

00:04:34.649 --> 00:04:35.567 position:50% align:center
[INOSE whinmes]

00:04:35.650 --> 00:04:37.318 position:50% align:center
As for you two, Mira and Ao,

00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:39.487 position:50% align:center
I hope we'll have fun
together this year.

00:04:39.571 --> 00:04:42.490 position:50% align:center
Huh? Does this mean
you know about us, too?

00:04:42.574 --> 00:04:45.118 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE] Yes. You're both in
the astronomy group, right?

00:04:45.201 --> 00:04:46.745 position:50% align:center
[BOTH]
Huh?

00:04:46.828 --> 00:04:49.456 position:50% align:center
I'm impressed you know
so much about our club.

00:04:49.539 --> 00:04:51.875 position:50% align:center
My sister talked about
you guys at home all the time.

00:04:51.958 --> 00:04:53.043 position:50% align:center
How could I not?

00:04:53.126 --> 00:04:55.712 position:50% align:center
She said you were awesome,
and she had fun.

00:04:57.255 --> 00:05:00.258 position:50% align:center
Okay, so, I assume you
want to be in the geology group,

00:05:00.342 --> 00:05:01.468 position:50% align:center
right, Chikage?

00:05:01.551 --> 00:05:03.261 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE] Yes. I fell
in love with rocks,

00:05:03.345 --> 00:05:04.721 position:50% align:center
thanks to my sister.

00:05:04.804 --> 00:05:08.183 position:50% align:center
And I love power stones
and fortune-telling, too.

00:05:08.266 --> 00:05:10.935 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
That's super exciting!

00:05:11.019 --> 00:05:12.729 position:50% align:center
I'm sure it'll be
a big hit in the newsletter

00:05:12.812 --> 00:05:14.647 position:50% align:center
and the cultural festival!

00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:16.483 position:50% align:center
My sister was right about you.

00:05:16.566 --> 00:05:18.068 position:50% align:center
You're totally adorable.

00:05:18.151 --> 00:05:19.069 position:50% align:center
[INOSE gasps]

00:05:19.152 --> 00:05:20.987 position:50% align:center
So, uh, I think...

00:05:21.071 --> 00:05:23.406 position:50% align:center
...there's something you should
know before we get started.

00:05:23.490 --> 00:05:27.285 position:50% align:center
Our club is composed of two
groups: astronomy and geology.

00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:29.662 position:50% align:center
Yes, I know.
I came to your cafÃ©.

00:05:29.746 --> 00:05:31.039 position:50% align:center
At the festival?

00:05:31.122 --> 00:05:33.958 position:50% align:center
Did you really?
And what did you think about it?

00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:35.960 position:50% align:center
Well... I enjoyed it,
but frankly,

00:05:36.044 --> 00:05:38.088 position:50% align:center
it left something to be desired.

00:05:40.006 --> 00:05:41.549 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Yoo-hoo!

00:05:41.633 --> 00:05:43.927 position:50% align:center
Megu said she wanted to visit
the Earth Sciences Club,

00:05:44.010 --> 00:05:45.553 position:50% align:center
so I-- What's going on?

00:05:45.637 --> 00:05:48.056 position:50% align:center
I have a feeling
we might have made a mistake.

00:05:48.139 --> 00:05:49.641 position:50% align:center
No. It's fine.

00:05:49.724 --> 00:05:52.686 position:50% align:center
This is Suzu, a second-year
and her sister, Megu.

00:05:52.769 --> 00:05:54.104 position:50% align:center
They're not club members.

00:05:54.187 --> 00:05:57.023 position:50% align:center
But they helped with
the cafÃ© for the festival.

00:05:57.107 --> 00:05:58.358 position:50% align:center
Your sweets are
the tastiest things

00:05:58.441 --> 00:06:00.026 position:50% align:center
I've ever had in my life!

00:06:00.110 --> 00:06:02.487 position:50% align:center
Aw, man. I like her already!

00:06:02.570 --> 00:06:05.073 position:50% align:center
So, um... What were
you just saying before?

00:06:05.156 --> 00:06:06.783 position:50% align:center
How was our cafÃ© lacking?

00:06:06.866 --> 00:06:08.618 position:50% align:center
Your displays
for the cultural festival

00:06:08.702 --> 00:06:09.994 position:50% align:center
were well-made.

00:06:10.078 --> 00:06:12.497 position:50% align:center
And your sweets were
delicious and lovely to look at.

00:06:12.580 --> 00:06:13.498 position:50% align:center
But...

00:06:13.581 --> 00:06:15.208 position:50% align:center
As the Earth Sciences Club,

00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:17.252 position:50% align:center
I think you have a
responsibility and should be

00:06:17.335 --> 00:06:18.920 position:50% align:center
more aware of the issues.

00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:21.214 position:50% align:center
[SUZU]
Which issues do you mean?

00:06:21.297 --> 00:06:22.841 position:50% align:center
Let me just put it this way.

00:06:22.924 --> 00:06:24.551 position:50% align:center
I don't want to
pursue astronomy.

00:06:24.634 --> 00:06:28.430 position:50% align:center
Or geology.
I want to go into meteorology.

00:06:28.513 --> 00:06:30.890 position:50% align:center
I believe we have a duty to
explore weather and climate,

00:06:30.974 --> 00:06:32.851 position:50% align:center
and how they affect us all!

00:06:38.064 --> 00:06:41.359 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] What she said
really made me think.

00:06:41.443 --> 00:06:44.571 position:50% align:center
She really seems like
such a conscientious person.

00:06:44.654 --> 00:06:47.532 position:50% align:center
That's a new field,
and a new goal for us as a club.

00:06:47.615 --> 00:06:49.909 position:50% align:center
I wonder if the new Earth
Sciences Club can live up to

00:06:49.993 --> 00:06:51.745 position:50% align:center
her expectations
and help her figure out

00:06:51.828 --> 00:06:53.955 position:50% align:center
what she wants to achieve.

00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:55.373 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA sigh]

00:06:59.377 --> 00:07:00.420 position:50% align:center
[YUUKO]
Don't be shy, now.

00:07:00.503 --> 00:07:02.213 position:50% align:center
Plenty more where
that came from!

00:07:02.297 --> 00:07:03.673 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna fatten you up!

00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:06.092 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Thanks, it looks delicious.

00:07:06.176 --> 00:07:07.635 position:50% align:center
--Here!
--Oh, thank you.

00:07:07.719 --> 00:07:10.847 position:50% align:center
[MIRA giggles] I'm starting
to learn what you like, Ao!

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:12.015 position:50% align:center
[YUUKO]
Oh, I forgot.

00:07:12.098 --> 00:07:13.725 position:50% align:center
Some mail came for
both of you, from, uh...

00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:15.935 position:50% align:center
The National
Astronomical Observatory?

00:07:16.019 --> 00:07:17.228 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA gasp]

00:07:17.562 --> 00:07:21.024 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I hope this will
help us discover our asteroid!

00:07:21.107 --> 00:07:23.902 position:50% align:center
Writing the short essay's
gonna be the hard part.

00:07:23.985 --> 00:07:26.571 position:50% align:center
Only seven people
get to participate.

00:07:26.654 --> 00:07:29.657 position:50% align:center
We've been working so hard,
studying and gathering data.

00:07:29.741 --> 00:07:31.618 position:50% align:center
I think we'll be all right.

00:07:31.701 --> 00:07:32.952 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Mm-hmm!

00:07:35.288 --> 00:07:37.332 position:50% align:center
A short essay on
my feelings about space

00:07:37.415 --> 00:07:39.668 position:50% align:center
and the stars?

00:07:39.751 --> 00:07:41.753 position:50% align:center
When I first met Ao,
it was her passion

00:07:41.836 --> 00:07:44.589 position:50% align:center
that made me want to
learn more about the stars.

00:07:44.673 --> 00:07:47.759 position:50% align:center
When I joined the Earth Sciences
Club, I learned about rocks

00:07:47.842 --> 00:07:50.679 position:50% align:center
and how fun it is to share
knowledge with everyone.

00:07:52.555 --> 00:07:53.890 position:50% align:center
That's it!

00:07:55.558 --> 00:07:56.685 position:50% align:center
[AO]
A barbecue?

00:07:56.768 --> 00:07:59.104 position:50% align:center
Yeah! Our club's
in its second year now,

00:07:59.187 --> 00:08:01.356 position:50% align:center
and I want it to be
as fun as last year was.

00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:02.440 position:50% align:center
So, I thought--

00:08:02.524 --> 00:08:03.817 position:50% align:center
What if we made
the club barbecue into

00:08:03.900 --> 00:08:05.485 position:50% align:center
an annual tradition?

00:08:05.568 --> 00:08:07.070 position:50% align:center
I love that idea.

00:08:07.153 --> 00:08:09.948 position:50% align:center
We should talk to Ino and Miss
Endou about it tomorrow, too!

00:08:10.031 --> 00:08:11.032 position:50% align:center
Yeah!

00:08:12.450 --> 00:08:15.036 position:50% align:center
I had already
put it on the calendar!

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:16.788 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Of course you did.

00:08:18.331 --> 00:08:20.250 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] This weekend, we're
having a barbecue to welcome

00:08:20.333 --> 00:08:21.584 position:50% align:center
our new members.

00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:23.795 position:50% align:center
Let us know if there's
anything you'd like to eat.

00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:25.296 position:50% align:center
Sounds like fun.

00:08:25.380 --> 00:08:27.340 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] We'll collect rocks
by the riverside

00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:31.261 position:50% align:center
and observe the stars and moon
while eating delicious food!

00:08:31.344 --> 00:08:33.304 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Not a care in the world.

00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:36.516 position:50% align:center
O... kay.

00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:38.727 position:50% align:center
She's surprisingly
adorable, right?

00:08:38.810 --> 00:08:40.145 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mm-hmm!

00:08:43.773 --> 00:08:45.358 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] White marshmallows,
yellow marshmallows,

00:08:45.442 --> 00:08:46.776 position:50% align:center
and pink marshmallows!

00:08:46.860 --> 00:08:48.778 position:50% align:center
Wow, say that five times fast!

00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:51.531 position:50% align:center
Mira. I think this is
marshmallow overkill.

00:08:51.614 --> 00:08:54.701 position:50% align:center
Look, I just want
Nanami to have a good time!

00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.245 position:50% align:center
[AO] Of course those are
the ones that she grabbed.

00:08:57.328 --> 00:08:59.873 position:50% align:center
Now all we've got left
to do is prepare the food!

00:08:59.956 --> 00:09:02.751 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Yeah! It's been so long
since our last barbecue.

00:09:02.834 --> 00:09:04.002 position:50% align:center
I can't wait!

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:08.006 position:50% align:center
[whines]

00:09:08.089 --> 00:09:09.132 position:50% align:center
The weather
report said it was

00:09:09.215 --> 00:09:10.967 position:50% align:center
gonna be cloudy, not rainy!

00:09:11.051 --> 00:09:12.719 position:50% align:center
I'd say we should postpone it.

00:09:12.802 --> 00:09:15.638 position:50% align:center
Except for the fact that we
already bought all the food.

00:09:15.722 --> 00:09:18.641 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] Location change!
I'll meet you at the station!

00:09:18.725 --> 00:09:21.186 position:50% align:center
--I called Suzu about it, too!
--[AO] Miss Endou.

00:09:21.269 --> 00:09:22.979 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
That's our barbecue magistrate!

00:09:23.063 --> 00:09:24.439 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
See you later!

00:09:28.526 --> 00:09:29.903 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Interesting.

00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:32.113 position:50% align:center
[AO] We won't have to worry
about the rain under here.

00:09:32.197 --> 00:09:34.741 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] It was already raining
like this when I woke up.

00:09:34.824 --> 00:09:36.701 position:50% align:center
I really didn't
want to reschedule.

00:09:36.785 --> 00:09:38.703 position:50% align:center
So I did a quick search
for places with shelter

00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:40.080 position:50% align:center
from the rain.

00:09:40.163 --> 00:09:42.123 position:50% align:center
Thank you for bringing
bread again this year, Suzu.

00:09:42.207 --> 00:09:44.584 position:50% align:center
No, problem--
I'm just happy to be here!

00:09:44.668 --> 00:09:47.003 position:50% align:center
Anyway, I'll leave
you girls to do your thing.

00:09:47.087 --> 00:09:49.422 position:50% align:center
Wake me up when the
meat's ready, 'kay?

00:09:49.506 --> 00:09:51.091 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE, NANAMI]
Huh?

00:09:52.467 --> 00:09:54.469 position:50% align:center
[AO] I can't believe it's
raining on our first event

00:09:54.552 --> 00:09:55.929 position:50% align:center
of the new school year.

00:09:56.012 --> 00:09:57.639 position:50% align:center
[INOSE]
Rain's not a problem here!

00:09:57.722 --> 00:10:00.642 position:50% align:center
I brought lots of tissues
for us to ward off the rain!

00:10:00.725 --> 00:10:02.686 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Oh! I get it!

00:10:02.769 --> 00:10:06.147 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] Oh my gosh, Ino,
could you be any cuter?

00:10:06.231 --> 00:10:08.400 position:50% align:center
I'm sure it'll clear up
if we make a bunch!

00:10:08.483 --> 00:10:10.610 position:50% align:center
And we're working together!

00:10:10.694 --> 00:10:12.028 position:50% align:center
I think it'd be
better to start getting

00:10:12.112 --> 00:10:14.155 position:50% align:center
the barbecue set up, honestly.

00:10:14.239 --> 00:10:16.991 position:50% align:center
They're just as
unbothered as my sister said.

00:10:32.173 --> 00:10:34.092 position:50% align:center
You all seem to have
this whole thing down.

00:10:34.175 --> 00:10:36.553 position:50% align:center
Well, we did it last
year, and the year before, too.

00:10:36.636 --> 00:10:39.889 position:50% align:center
Wait, this whole exchange
feels a bit like dÃ©jÃ  vu to me.

00:10:39.973 --> 00:10:41.474 position:50% align:center
If we were by the river,

00:10:41.558 --> 00:10:44.144 position:50% align:center
we would have collected rocks
and done some major stargazing.

00:10:44.227 --> 00:10:46.354 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
We can't do either here, sadly.

00:10:46.438 --> 00:10:49.357 position:50% align:center
Welp, Chika and Nana. Sorry.

00:10:49.441 --> 00:10:50.734 position:50% align:center
You're Chika?

00:10:50.817 --> 00:10:51.818 position:50% align:center
You're Nana?

00:10:51.901 --> 00:10:53.486 position:50% align:center
Mira assigning
nicknames to everyone

00:10:53.570 --> 00:10:55.655 position:50% align:center
totally feels like dÃ©jÃ  vu, too!

00:10:55.739 --> 00:10:57.198 position:50% align:center
[SUZU humming]

00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.285 position:50% align:center
That smells good.

00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:02.037 position:50% align:center
What are you making over there?

00:11:02.120 --> 00:11:04.622 position:50% align:center
[SUZU giggles]
Oh, just wait and see!

00:11:11.379 --> 00:11:13.173 position:50% align:center
These kebabs are so good.

00:11:13.256 --> 00:11:16.718 position:50% align:center
Yep, I agree! Sometimes,
food tastes better outside.

00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:18.762 position:50% align:center
But this rain though...

00:11:18.845 --> 00:11:22.182 position:50% align:center
[AO] Looks like it's
pouring even harder now.

00:11:22.265 --> 00:11:25.560 position:50% align:center
I think... It's gonna
slack up in about an hour or so.

00:11:25.643 --> 00:11:27.187 position:50% align:center
Are you some
kind of witch who can

00:11:27.270 --> 00:11:29.022 position:50% align:center
