00:11:35.070 --> 00:11:37.072 position:50% align:center
No, um... I just
checked the weather app

00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:38.448 position:50% align:center
on my phone.

00:11:38.531 --> 00:11:40.575 position:50% align:center
Doesn't your technique also
get your shoes dirty?

00:11:40.658 --> 00:11:42.077 position:50% align:center
Oh, right.

00:11:43.661 --> 00:11:45.622 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
That was so good!

00:11:47.374 --> 00:11:50.043 position:50% align:center
[AO] So, you want to
focus on meteorology.

00:11:50.126 --> 00:11:51.711 position:50% align:center
Like, weather reporting
and stuff?

00:11:51.795 --> 00:11:52.962 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
And more.

00:11:53.046 --> 00:11:55.173 position:50% align:center
It deals with all things
related to the weather.

00:11:55.256 --> 00:11:56.925 position:50% align:center
Wind, clouds, atmosphere.

00:11:57.008 --> 00:11:59.552 position:50% align:center
As well as natural disasters.

00:11:59.636 --> 00:12:02.389 position:50% align:center
Uh, you don't sound
too happy about it.

00:12:02.472 --> 00:12:04.808 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI] How could I be,
after my relatives suffered

00:12:04.891 --> 00:12:06.142 position:50% align:center
so much because of it?

00:12:06.226 --> 00:12:07.936 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Huh?

00:12:08.019 --> 00:12:09.854 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
It happened three years ago.

00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:13.441 position:50% align:center
A flood devastated
my aunt and uncle's home.

00:12:13.525 --> 00:12:16.444 position:50% align:center
Fortunately, nobody was
injured or anything.

00:12:16.528 --> 00:12:20.156 position:50% align:center
But I never want to see my
aunt cry like that ever again.

00:12:20.240 --> 00:12:21.825 position:50% align:center
I'm sorry that happened.

00:12:21.908 --> 00:12:23.159 position:50% align:center
It fuels me.

00:12:23.243 --> 00:12:25.870 position:50% align:center
My need to stop it from
happening to anyone else.

00:12:25.954 --> 00:12:27.372 position:50% align:center
[AO, MIRA sigh]

00:12:31.334 --> 00:12:33.211 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
Hey, Nanami? Here.

00:12:33.294 --> 00:12:35.005 position:50% align:center
You should have this.

00:12:35.088 --> 00:12:36.506 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
It's blue lace agate.

00:12:36.589 --> 00:12:39.092 position:50% align:center
Sometimes people
call it sky blue onyx.

00:12:39.175 --> 00:12:40.677 position:50% align:center
It's said to be calming.

00:12:40.760 --> 00:12:43.221 position:50% align:center
And can help you
release difficult emotions.

00:12:44.556 --> 00:12:46.975 position:50% align:center
Just be careful
of pushing yourself too hard.

00:12:47.058 --> 00:12:49.477 position:50% align:center
I don't think I'm
pushing myself too hard at all.

00:12:50.353 --> 00:12:52.355 position:50% align:center
What's that? I'm confused.

00:12:52.439 --> 00:12:53.648 position:50% align:center
Between your eyebrows.

00:12:53.732 --> 00:12:54.899 position:50% align:center
There's a wrinkle.

00:12:56.943 --> 00:12:59.320 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Okay. Thanks, I guess?

00:12:59.404 --> 00:13:01.281 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE] It seems to
me like meteorology hits

00:13:01.364 --> 00:13:03.116 position:50% align:center
really close to home for you.

00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:06.036 position:50% align:center
Well. It's more
useful than other sciences.

00:13:06.119 --> 00:13:08.872 position:50% align:center
Unlike astronomy and geology,
it helps people be prepared

00:13:08.955 --> 00:13:10.415 position:50% align:center
and can even save lives.

00:13:10.498 --> 00:13:12.167 position:50% align:center
Astronomy helps people, too!

00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:14.336 position:50% align:center
You can't launch satellites
that monitor weather!

00:13:14.419 --> 00:13:16.963 position:50% align:center
Or watch small
astronomical objects to see

00:13:17.047 --> 00:13:18.340 position:50% align:center
if they'll hit Earth!

00:13:18.423 --> 00:13:20.842 position:50% align:center
Geology can help people
with their daily lives, too!

00:13:20.925 --> 00:13:23.595 position:50% align:center
Like, um, I can't think of
any examples right now,

00:13:23.678 --> 00:13:25.055 position:50% align:center
but I know it's true!

00:13:25.138 --> 00:13:26.931 position:50% align:center
It helps predict
earthquakes and allows us

00:13:27.015 --> 00:13:29.642 position:50% align:center
to excavate minerals
that we use every day.

00:13:29.726 --> 00:13:32.062 position:50% align:center
Some stones have the power
to make people feel happier

00:13:32.145 --> 00:13:33.646 position:50% align:center
and more at peace.

00:13:33.730 --> 00:13:36.107 position:50% align:center
That last one got
a little pseudo-sciencey.

00:13:36.191 --> 00:13:37.650 position:50% align:center
Agreed.

00:13:42.822 --> 00:13:45.784 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI'S AUNT] Photos, videos,
letters--our family history,

00:13:45.867 --> 00:13:47.827 position:50% align:center
ruined by the mud.

00:13:47.911 --> 00:13:50.121 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
My poor Aunt.

00:13:50.205 --> 00:13:51.706 position:50% align:center
I hate the rain.

00:13:51.790 --> 00:13:54.167 position:50% align:center
I hate that filthy,
stinking mud.

00:13:54.250 --> 00:13:57.379 position:50% align:center
And I hate how useless I feel.

00:13:57.462 --> 00:14:00.757 position:50% align:center
I'm just doing what
I feel like I have to do.

00:14:00.840 --> 00:14:02.509 position:50% align:center
[MIRA gasps]

00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:05.220 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] Well... The rain
finally dried up, huh?

00:14:05.303 --> 00:14:07.430 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] Aren't you glad I
brought all those tissues?

00:14:07.514 --> 00:14:09.557 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Hey. Is that a...?

00:14:09.641 --> 00:14:10.767 position:50% align:center
Look, Nana!

00:14:10.850 --> 00:14:12.894 position:50% align:center
A rainbow!

00:14:12.977 --> 00:14:13.895 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:14:13.978 --> 00:14:16.106 position:50% align:center
A circumhorizontal arc!

00:14:16.189 --> 00:14:17.732 position:50% align:center
A what, now?

00:14:17.816 --> 00:14:19.234 position:50% align:center
In atmospheric optics,

00:14:19.317 --> 00:14:22.445 position:50% align:center
they call it a circumhorizontal
arc, instead of a rainbow.

00:14:22.529 --> 00:14:24.072 position:50% align:center
It's the light
refracting off hexagonal

00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:26.741 position:50% align:center
ice crystals that creates
the rainbow colors.

00:14:26.825 --> 00:14:29.160 position:50% align:center
It's a fairly rare phenomenon.

00:14:29.244 --> 00:14:31.663 position:50% align:center
This is actually my first time
seeing one in real life,

00:14:31.746 --> 00:14:33.164 position:50% align:center
believe it or not.

00:14:33.248 --> 00:14:35.208 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI gasps]

00:14:35.291 --> 00:14:36.918 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasping]

00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:40.422 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Ahem!

00:14:40.505 --> 00:14:42.799 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Interesting! Hey, I know!

00:14:42.882 --> 00:14:44.801 position:50% align:center
--We should take a picture!
--[AO] Yeah!

00:14:44.884 --> 00:14:46.511 position:50% align:center
[INOSE] This will be great
for our newsletter!

00:14:46.594 --> 00:14:48.805 position:50% align:center
Seems like you've
studied an awful lot, Nanami.

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:50.765 position:50% align:center
--[gasps]
--[MIRA] Okay!

00:14:50.849 --> 00:14:52.600 position:50% align:center
Well, I have a big goal.

00:14:52.684 --> 00:14:54.477 position:50% align:center
It's what you do.

00:14:54.561 --> 00:14:56.062 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] Yeah, but I think
studying with the goal

00:14:56.146 --> 00:14:59.899 position:50% align:center
of helping others is remarkable,
especially for someone your age.

00:14:59.983 --> 00:15:01.484 position:50% align:center
If you don't mind my saying so,

00:15:01.568 --> 00:15:03.820 position:50% align:center
I do think you can honor
your own feelings more.

00:15:03.903 --> 00:15:05.613 position:50% align:center
Especially the part
of you that finds the joy

00:15:05.697 --> 00:15:07.866 position:50% align:center
and fun in studying.

00:15:07.949 --> 00:15:10.869 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE] Your wrinkle's gone,
too, just like the rain.

00:15:10.952 --> 00:15:12.328 position:50% align:center
Let's take the picture quickly

00:15:12.412 --> 00:15:15.248 position:50% align:center
before the rainbow's gone.
Right, Nanami?

00:15:15.331 --> 00:15:17.334 position:50% align:center
I like the name
Mira gave me today.

00:15:17.417 --> 00:15:18.752 position:50% align:center
Call me Nana.

00:15:18.835 --> 00:15:21.254 position:50% align:center
Well, let's do this
then, 'kay, Nana?

00:15:21.338 --> 00:15:23.214 position:50% align:center
[chuckles]

00:15:23.298 --> 00:15:26.426 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] Everyone!
The baumkuchen's ready!

00:15:26.509 --> 00:15:28.178 position:50% align:center
The what, now?

00:15:28.261 --> 00:15:30.472 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS gasping]

00:15:30.555 --> 00:15:31.681 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
Awesome!

00:15:31.765 --> 00:15:33.350 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU]
It's perfect!

00:15:33.433 --> 00:15:35.435 position:50% align:center
[GROUP]
Thanks for the food!

00:15:36.770 --> 00:15:39.147 position:50% align:center
I love how you can
see the strata, too!

00:15:39.230 --> 00:15:42.067 position:50% align:center
And they're bent, so these
are called "folded strata!"

00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:43.902 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI] "Baum" means tree,
so wouldn't these be

00:15:43.985 --> 00:15:45.612 position:50% align:center
more like age rings?

00:15:45.695 --> 00:15:47.614 position:50% align:center
We get it. You're smart.

00:15:49.074 --> 00:15:52.118 position:50% align:center
Well. I'm glad
you're all enjoying it!

00:15:52.202 --> 00:15:54.245 position:50% align:center
By the way, who's
the genius that charred

00:15:54.329 --> 00:15:55.538 position:50% align:center
these marshmallows?

00:15:55.622 --> 00:15:59.292 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I spent good money
on those marshmallows.

00:15:59.376 --> 00:16:01.252 position:50% align:center
I think the burnt ones
are the best.

00:16:01.336 --> 00:16:03.672 position:50% align:center
[laughter]

00:16:09.219 --> 00:16:11.388 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Ahh, I had so much fun!

00:16:11.471 --> 00:16:13.473 position:50% align:center
[SUZU] I have to go help
prep for the morning.

00:16:13.556 --> 00:16:14.474 position:50% align:center
See you guys!

00:16:14.557 --> 00:16:16.518 position:50% align:center
Bye! Thanks for coming today!

00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:19.521 position:50% align:center
I only wish
this lovely weather had

00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:21.606 position:50% align:center
shown up sooner, don't you?

00:16:21.690 --> 00:16:24.025 position:50% align:center
Well, then. What do you all say
we stick it out a bit,

00:16:24.109 --> 00:16:25.485 position:50% align:center
until the stars come out?

00:16:25.568 --> 00:16:26.695 position:50% align:center
[GIRLS]
Hmm?

00:16:26.778 --> 00:16:28.238 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
When the weather is clear,

00:16:28.321 --> 00:16:31.658 position:50% align:center
we seize the opportunity to
practice using the telescope!

00:16:31.741 --> 00:16:33.118 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Go ahead.

00:16:34.703 --> 00:16:36.454 position:50% align:center
The moon is so beautiful.

00:16:36.538 --> 00:16:40.125 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Isn't it? The one you see
right next to it is Jupiter.

00:16:40.208 --> 00:16:42.669 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE] What's the
magnification power on this?

00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:44.254 position:50% align:center
Oh. Lemme see.

00:16:44.337 --> 00:16:47.173 position:50% align:center
The barrel's focal length
is 910 millimeters,

00:16:47.257 --> 00:16:50.927 position:50% align:center
the ocular lens is 15
millimeters, so, uh, I guess,

00:16:51.011 --> 00:16:52.345 position:50% align:center
that means...

00:16:52.429 --> 00:16:55.348 position:50% align:center
With this lens, there's
about 60 times magnification.

00:16:55.432 --> 00:16:58.351 position:50% align:center
Why don't you try
adjusting the angle?

00:16:58.435 --> 00:16:59.936 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI]
There, I got it!

00:17:00.020 --> 00:17:01.896 position:50% align:center
It's amazing that
you can get a picture like that

00:17:01.980 --> 00:17:03.273 position:50% align:center
with a smartphone camera.

00:17:03.356 --> 00:17:05.483 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we call that
a collimated photo.

00:17:05.567 --> 00:17:07.193 position:50% align:center
While you may not
be familiar with it.

00:17:07.277 --> 00:17:10.071 position:50% align:center
you do have a knack
for it, Nanami.

00:17:10.155 --> 00:17:11.448 position:50% align:center
You can call me Nana.

00:17:11.531 --> 00:17:13.658 position:50% align:center
[giggles]

00:17:13.742 --> 00:17:15.994 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] That reminds me,
how are those short essays

00:17:16.077 --> 00:17:17.328 position:50% align:center
coming along, you two?

00:17:17.412 --> 00:17:21.166 position:50% align:center
[NANAMI] Short essays?
The Shining Star Challenge?

00:17:21.249 --> 00:17:22.751 position:50% align:center
[AO] Yeah, the essays
are like a test

00:17:22.834 --> 00:17:24.961 position:50% align:center
to qualify for participation.

00:17:25.045 --> 00:17:26.671 position:50% align:center
They're not quite finished yet,

00:17:26.755 --> 00:17:29.382 position:50% align:center
but we've been working together
every night to polish them.

00:17:29.466 --> 00:17:31.009 position:50% align:center
Wait, every night?

00:17:31.092 --> 00:17:34.304 position:50% align:center
Don't tell me you two ignore
your curfew like delinquents!

00:17:34.387 --> 00:17:35.930 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Hmm? Heh...

00:17:36.014 --> 00:17:37.557 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
Ao's parents moved away, and,

00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:40.769 position:50% align:center
since Ao and Mira are trying to
discover an asteroid together,

00:17:40.852 --> 00:17:42.562 position:50% align:center
their parents are
letting Ao stay in Mira's

00:17:42.645 --> 00:17:44.939 position:50% align:center
sister's old room.
Is that right?

00:17:45.023 --> 00:17:45.982 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mm-hmm.

00:17:46.066 --> 00:17:47.776 position:50% align:center
Ao's parents moved away?

00:17:47.859 --> 00:17:49.986 position:50% align:center
It's not easy to live
apart from your family

00:17:50.070 --> 00:17:51.654 position:50% align:center
as a teenager.

00:17:51.738 --> 00:17:53.406 position:50% align:center
Um, what's the matter?

00:17:53.490 --> 00:17:54.908 position:50% align:center
My sister...!

00:17:59.662 --> 00:18:01.164 position:50% align:center
What is that?

00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:02.415 position:50% align:center
Fortune-telling.

00:18:02.499 --> 00:18:04.959 position:50% align:center
Specifically geomancy.

00:18:05.043 --> 00:18:06.294 position:50% align:center
You read the stones.

00:18:06.378 --> 00:18:09.464 position:50% align:center
I wanted to tell their fortunes.

00:18:09.547 --> 00:18:11.925 position:50% align:center
--I see.
--Huh?

00:18:12.008 --> 00:18:13.510 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
Isolation.

00:18:13.593 --> 00:18:15.637 position:50% align:center
But the stones say they should
continue to move forward

00:18:15.720 --> 00:18:17.097 position:50% align:center
with their goals.

00:18:19.557 --> 00:18:22.560 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Huh? No way, for real?

00:18:22.644 --> 00:18:23.770 position:50% align:center
I did it!

00:18:23.853 --> 00:18:24.813 position:50% align:center
I can't believe it.

00:18:24.896 --> 00:18:26.398 position:50% align:center
I passed the written screening!

00:18:26.481 --> 00:18:27.399 position:50% align:center
That's awesome!

00:18:27.482 --> 00:18:28.942 position:50% align:center
[EVE]
Wow, congratulations!

00:18:29.025 --> 00:18:29.984 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:18:30.068 --> 00:18:32.112 position:50% align:center
That's worth celibrating!

00:18:32.195 --> 00:18:34.072 position:50% align:center
This is a really juicy scoop!

00:18:34.155 --> 00:18:36.574 position:50% align:center
I'm gonna write an article
about it for the paper!

00:18:36.658 --> 00:18:39.369 position:50% align:center
We'd love to go there with you
to cover the whole process.

00:18:39.452 --> 00:18:41.496 position:50% align:center
But, alas, it's not
in the club budget.

00:18:41.579 --> 00:18:43.665 position:50% align:center
So, instead...

00:18:43.748 --> 00:18:45.125 position:50% align:center
...I compiled this
packet of products

00:18:45.208 --> 00:18:47.043 position:50% align:center
unique to Ishigaki island!

00:18:47.127 --> 00:18:48.795 position:50% align:center
You can use it as a reference
when you're picking out

00:18:48.878 --> 00:18:50.171 position:50% align:center
souvenirs for all of us!

00:18:50.255 --> 00:18:52.549 position:50% align:center
Jeez, Eve, you're
getting out of control now.

00:18:52.632 --> 00:18:55.260 position:50% align:center
Try to rein it in
a little bit, will ya?

00:18:55.343 --> 00:18:57.804 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Sorry.

00:18:57.887 --> 00:19:00.181 position:50% align:center
I didn't make it.

00:19:00.265 --> 00:19:01.516 position:50% align:center
[USAMI, EVE, MIRA]
Huh?!

00:19:03.309 --> 00:19:04.561 position:50% align:center
Oh, no...

00:19:04.644 --> 00:19:07.647 position:50% align:center
I think I just saw
them both die on the inside.

00:19:07.731 --> 00:19:09.566 position:50% align:center
Only one of them passed?

00:19:09.649 --> 00:19:11.943 position:50% align:center
It seems like Chika's
fortune was spot-on.

00:19:12.027 --> 00:19:13.611 position:50% align:center
This is so stupid!

00:19:13.695 --> 00:19:14.863 position:50% align:center
But keep your chin up--

00:19:14.946 --> 00:19:16.781 position:50% align:center
opportunity can close
doors and open windows!

00:19:16.865 --> 00:19:19.909 position:50% align:center
Stop it! Now is not
the time for empty clichÃ©s!

00:19:19.993 --> 00:19:21.286 position:50% align:center
[CHIKAGE]
Here, look at this.

00:19:22.954 --> 00:19:24.622 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Mira! Ao!

00:19:24.706 --> 00:19:26.041 position:50% align:center
What are you two sulking for?

00:19:26.124 --> 00:19:28.251 position:50% align:center
[MORINO]
Yoo-hoo! Long time no see!

00:19:28.335 --> 00:19:30.670 position:50% align:center
Sakurai, Monroe,
is that really you?

00:19:30.754 --> 00:19:32.922 position:50% align:center
[INOSE whimpers]

00:19:33.006 --> 00:19:34.758 position:50% align:center
Hey! Ino, why are you crying?

00:19:34.841 --> 00:19:36.468 position:50% align:center
I just find it so
reassuring to hear

00:19:36.551 --> 00:19:40.638 position:50% align:center
our former leaders'
voices at a time like this!

00:19:40.722 --> 00:19:42.599 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
Chikage told me what happened.

00:19:42.682 --> 00:19:44.601 position:50% align:center
You don't have time
to waste moping.

00:19:44.684 --> 00:19:46.644 position:50% align:center
I mean, you cleared
a major hurdle.

00:19:46.728 --> 00:19:50.315 position:50% align:center
[MORINO] Mm! Besides. Even if
only one of you can go,

00:19:50.398 --> 00:19:52.025 position:50% align:center
you can still share the
knowledge you gain there

00:19:52.108 --> 00:19:53.318 position:50% align:center
with each other.

00:19:53.401 --> 00:19:54.444 position:50% align:center
[SAKURAI]
We're still here.

00:19:54.527 --> 00:19:56.279 position:50% align:center
If you need anything,
just reach out.

00:19:56.363 --> 00:19:59.199 position:50% align:center
Right! Thank you both so much!

00:19:59.282 --> 00:20:00.742 position:50% align:center
Later!

00:20:00.825 --> 00:20:01.993 position:50% align:center
Oh, dang it.

00:20:02.077 --> 00:20:04.496 position:50% align:center
I totally forgot
to congratulate Mira.

00:20:04.579 --> 00:20:08.875 position:50% align:center
Oh, Sakura.
You haven't changed at all!

00:20:08.958 --> 00:20:10.752 position:50% align:center
"While you may feel isolated.

00:20:10.835 --> 00:20:13.505 position:50% align:center
The path ahead will open up
your life to new opportunities

00:20:13.588 --> 00:20:14.839 position:50% align:center
and adventures.

00:20:14.923 --> 00:20:17.258 position:50% align:center
Abandon your old values
and forge ahead with faith

00:20:17.342 --> 00:20:19.135 position:50% align:center
in your intuition."

00:20:19.219 --> 00:20:21.971 position:50% align:center
That's your fortune,
according to the stones.

00:20:22.055 --> 00:20:24.557 position:50% align:center
I hope you find it
helpful in some way.

00:20:24.641 --> 00:20:26.017 position:50% align:center
[MIRA sighs]

00:20:27.185 --> 00:20:30.105 position:50% align:center
Miss Endou just told me
that she would be my chaperone.

00:20:30.188 --> 00:20:31.314 position:50% align:center
Well, that's a relief.

00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:33.566 position:50% align:center
I know. I would
probably get lost if

00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:38.822 position:50% align:center
I had to travel... to Okinawa...
all by myself...

00:20:38.905 --> 00:20:39.864 position:50% align:center
Mira?

00:20:39.948 --> 00:20:41.116 position:50% align:center
[MIRA whimpers]

00:20:41.199 --> 00:20:43.868 position:50% align:center
I just wanted us to be
doing all this together!

00:20:43.952 --> 00:20:46.830 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Ah! Listen!

00:20:46.913 --> 00:20:48.623 position:50% align:center
You have to suck it up
and move on.

00:20:48.707 --> 00:20:51.167 position:50% align:center
What everyone said is right:
this is a great opportunity,

00:20:51.251 --> 00:20:52.502 position:50% align:center
so seize it!

00:20:52.585 --> 00:20:54.546 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Yeah. True...

00:20:54.629 --> 00:20:55.672 position:50% align:center
And in the meantime,

00:20:55.755 --> 00:20:58.550 position:50% align:center
I'll be thinking
of ways I can help.

00:20:58.633 --> 00:21:01.428 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Hold on.
Has Ao gotten stronger?

00:21:03.680 --> 00:21:04.973 position:50% align:center
[AO sighs]

00:21:15.233 --> 00:21:17.444 position:50% align:center
This is it! I'm heading out!

00:21:17.527 --> 00:21:18.570 position:50% align:center
Be careful.

00:21:18.653 --> 00:21:20.697 position:50% align:center
We'll be looking
forward to the results!

00:21:20.780 --> 00:21:23.324 position:50% align:center
Yes, and the cool souvenirs!

00:21:29.706 --> 00:21:31.833 position:50% align:center
Oh, Usami, they grow up so fast.

00:21:31.916 --> 00:21:33.168 position:50% align:center
It's just for a few days--

00:21:33.251 --> 00:21:35.545 position:50% align:center
not like she's going off to war.

00:21:35.628 --> 00:21:38.798 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] I'll call you
every day that I'm gone!

00:21:42.344 --> 00:21:44.679 position:50% align:center
It's so hot!

00:21:44.763 --> 00:21:47.474 position:50% align:center
[ENDOU] Okay. First order
of business: rent a car.

00:21:47.557 --> 00:21:48.558 position:50% align:center
[AO]
Mira!

00:21:51.353 --> 00:21:52.354 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:21:52.437 --> 00:21:54.105 position:50% align:center
Why are you...?

00:21:54.189 --> 00:21:55.440 position:50% align:center
[AO]
I...

00:21:55.523 --> 00:21:56.816 position:50% align:center
I'm here!

00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:58.693 position:50% align:center
[BOTH gasp]

00:21:58.777 --> 00:22:01.404 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Wha--? What do you mean?

00:22:02.697 --> 00:22:04.115 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
Why?

00:22:05.575 --> 00:22:07.494 position:50% align:center
[MIRA]
What's going on?

00:23:46.009 --> 00:23:49.304 position:50% align:center
[MIRA] Next time,
"Shining Star Challenge!"